= Vote of no confidence

Following the collapse of our coalition, President [+ president +] has appointed Heinrich Brüning of the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?] Party in a government supported by bourgeois forces. However, they cannot survive without the support from us or Hugenberg's <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. [? if constructive_vonc: Well actually, it can but it wouldn't be able to pass any legislation. ?]

Brüning, has reorganized his cabinet to include the parties to the right of the [? if not lvp_formed and dvp_exist: <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>?][? if not lvp_formed and not dvp_exist: <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>?], such as the new <span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span>, which has been granted generous cabinet positions. We are left with the choice to "tolerate" the government to prevent the gains of extremists within the Reichstag[? if not constructive_vonc:&nbsp;or vote to oust Brüning for new elections?].

[? if constructive_vonc: With the requirement that votes of no-confidence be constructive, the no-confidence motions put forward by the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> and the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> have no chance of succeeding. ?]

