We have successfully passed a motion of no confidence to replace Brüning with Breitscheid. We are now ruling in a united front with the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span>.

Whatever their reasoning is, the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> has control over the ministries of government.

@bruning_spd
title: Brüning approaches us.
subtitle: We are expected to provide "toleration" to a bourgeois government.
view-if: cordon_sanitaire >= 50 and constructive_vonc
on-arrival: rural_kvp += 3; rural_dnvp -= 3; old_middle_kvp += 3; old_middle_dnvp -= 3; new_middle_kvp += 3; new_middle_dnvp -= 3; spd_toleration_kvp = 1

With the only path towards a viable majority lying with us, Brüning has started negotiations to try to gain our support for his new government. With no way of bringing down Brüning's government, we are forced to provide "toleration" for the time being.

The <span style="color: #0087DC;">**KVP**</span> bolster their credentials against Hugenberg's "all or nothing" policy.
